[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m/*\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mClosure\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mA closure is an object, created from a block whose source first word after the\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34moptional tag is \"expose\".\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mA closure remembers the values of the variables defined in the outer environment\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mof the block. The behaviour of the closure is a method generated from the block,\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mwhich is attached to the closure under the name \"do\". The values of the captured"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mvariables are accessible from this method \"do\" using expose. Updating a variable\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mfrom the closure will have no impact on the original context (hence the name\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m\"closure by value\").\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "ooRexx[bash]> "]
